                <head>351. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On May 21, General <persName>Leon Cantave</persName>, Haitian Army Chief of
                    Staff, issued a proclamation dissolving the Executive Council and announcing
                    that the Army had assumed control of the government. <persName corresp="#p_FD1"
                        >Daniel Fignole</persName>, a former Army Chief of Staff, was sworn in as
                    Provisional President on May 26. At the 325th meeting of the National Security
                    Council on May 27, Director of Central Intelligence <persName corresp="#p_DAW1"
                        >Allen Dulles</persName> discussed the situation in Haiti. (Eisenhower
                    Library, Whitman File, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Records)</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_FD1">Fignole</persName> was forced into exile by an Army
                    coup on June 14. A Military Council of Government, headed by the new Army Chief
                    of <pb facs="0989" n="955" xml:id="pg_955"/> Staff <persName>Antonio
                        Kebreau</persName>, was formed. Documentation on these events is in
                    Department of State, Central Files 738.00 and 738.02.</p>
            </div>
